    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-04-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-04-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="856"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d856">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 882.51/323.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Special Representative</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 9, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your April 9. Department learns from the Minister at Monrovia that the Liberian
                    Government cabled £1,750 to pay interest on 1871 loan, on March 28, to the
                    Liberian Consul General at London. But the Department’s instructions of March 27
                    are for the present not changed thereby.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
